 while hearing remains normal.","dimension":9,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033536,0.040106,0.043627,0.047848,0.052899,0.063763,0.066597,0.080847,0.10805,0.13949,0.16728,0.15595],"unified_progress":[0.026645,0.040796,0.046722,0.053569,0.060736,0.074902,0.079158,0.094392,0.10518,0.11151,0.13678,0.16962]},{"section":22,"text":"These findings are classic for benign paroxysmal positional vertigo (BPPV), which is characterized by positional vertigo with nystagmus and normal hearing.","dimension":9,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.021518,0.028717,0.033752,0.038767,0.04265,0.050649,0.054089,0.065608,0.086696,0.13854,0.20648,0.23254],"unified_progress":[0.015299,0.025955,0.033224,0.040889,0.047372,0.059706,0.06572,0.08358,0.098903,0.11415,0.16546,0.24974]},{"section":23,"text":"No cardiac or neurological deficits are present, and the treadmill test is normal, further supporting a vestibular cause rather than a cardio\u2011cerebrovascular one.","dimension":15,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030537,0.044303,0.050147,0.053624,0.061206,0.067372,0.070934,0.079662,0.088656,0.13016,0.16574,0.15765],"unified_progress":[0.016329,0.033252,0.045211,0.054408,0.06594,0.075391,0.085888,0.10171,0.11285,0.13552,0.1361,0.1374]},{"section":24,"text":"Therefore, the most likely diagnosis is BPPV.","dimension":8,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.016468,0.025149,0.031784,0.042143,0.050753,0.06309,0.072713,0.085038,0.097305,0.10905,0.16437,0.24214],"unified_progress":[0.0096313,0.01886,0.025114,0.033041,0.039406,0.051774,0.058806,0.075942,0.091982,0.11278,0.181,0.30166]},{"section":25,"text":"<answer> Benign paroxysmal positional vertigo (BPPV) </answer>","dimension":18,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.010346,0.015447,0.018162,0.021114,0.023963,0.026756,0.02867,0.034725,0.038427,0.045493,0.064316,0.67258],"unified_progress":[0.0050018,0.010346,0.014804,0.02088,0.026977,0.040354,0.04649,0.069691,0.09